{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b2168174-bea6-4493-a168-27f1f1f3f017","content":"Here's what's likely wrong and how to fix each:\n\n**1. Exception on `GoToAsync(\"productdetails\")`**\n\nRoutes not in the Shell visual hierarchy must be explicitly registered:\n\n```csharp\n// In AppShell constructor or MauiProgram\nRouting.RegisterRoute(\"productdetails\", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));\n```\n\nThen navigate with: `GoToAsync(\"productdetails\")` (relative) or as a sub-route like `GoToAsync(\"//products/productdetails\")`.\n\n---\n\n**2. `GoToAsync(\"//products/active\")` — navigates but nothing changes**\n\nYour `Tab` or `ShellContent` elements likely don't have explicit `Route` properties, so the absolute path doesn't resolve to what you expect. Set them explicitly:\n\n```xml\n<FlyoutItem Route=\"products\">\n    <Tab Route=\"active\" Title=\"Active\">\n        <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate local:ActivePage}\" />\n    </Tab>\n</FlyoutItem>\n```\n\nAlso verify the target item isn't hidden (`IsVisible=\"False\"` or `FlyoutItemIsVisible=\"False\"`).\n\n---\n\n**3. 3-second startup with 12 pages**\n\nShell instantiates every page at startup if you assign `ContentPage` directly. Use `ContentTemplate` for lazy instantiation:\n\n```xml\n<!-- ❌ Slow: page created immediately -->\n<ShellContent>\n    <local:HeavyPage />\n</ShellContent>\n\n<!-- ✅ Fast: page created only when navigated to -->\n<ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate local:HeavyPage}\" />\n```\n\nApply `DataTemplate` to all 12 pages. Only the initially visible page gets created at launch; the rest are deferred.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"163fab33-cb30-4a6f-b1bf-149934dad12c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about three common .NET MAUI Shell navigation issues. These are well-known problems with known solutions. I can answer directly from my knowledge without needing to search any codebase.\n\n1. **GoToAsync(\"productdetails\") throws an exception** - The route isn't registered. In MAUI Shell, routes that aren't defined in the Shell visual hierarchy must be registered with `Routing.RegisterRoute`.\n\n2. **GoToAsync(\"//products/active\") navigates but nothing visible changes** - This is likely because multiple ShellContent items share the same ContentPage type or the route structure has duplicate content templates. More commonly, this happens when the route resolves to the same page that's already displayed (e.g., the Tab/ShellContent is already selected), or when using implicit routes that point to the same page instance.\n   \n   The absolute route `//products/active` might successfully navigate but produce no visual change if the Shell hierarchy already displays that content, or if the ShellContent/Tab elements lack explicit `Route` properties, causing the navigation to resolve incorrectly or land on an already-active page. The most likely culprit is missing explicit `Route` properties on the Shell hierarchy—when you navigate to `//products/active`, Shell needs `Route=\"products\"` on the Tab and `Route=\"active\"` on the ShellContent, otherwise it generates implicit routes from class names and your navigation might resolve to the wrong section or a hidden item. For the startup performance issue, the solution is switching from creating all pages upfront to using `ContentTemplate` with `DataTemplate` for lazy loading, so pages only instantiate when you actually navigate to them.","outputTokens":1196,"requestId":"0816:371ABE:A6E799:C21DDC:69F2AAE2"},"id":"cb0d538a-00b3-45b1-88b3-55283c2d1633","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:06:07.207Z","parentId":"18b20311-9a5c-4a38-be7e-8178edca19c6"}
